Hello from Le Marais. Thank you to everyone who told me to stay in this neighborhood 😍

Montmartre… hard for me to say, impossible for me to spell, not hard for me to love.

#montmartre #sacrecoeur #parisfrance #facadelovers #cntraveler #cityliving #tlpicks #renoir #prettycities

That’s a wrap on Paris—we’ll be back! 🇫🇷 

Highlights: An incredible meal at @guysavoy’s, cocktails at @littlereddoorparis, falafel at @lasdufallafel (and magically, no line), seafood at @chezjanou, walking around Montmartre, and bumping into fellow New Yorker, @kevinjamesdoyle! 🍷 

Lows: Tour groups at the Louvre. And, at least in December, the Eiffel Tower is better from the ground. 

What an incredibly gorgeous city full of wine, butter, and art. Now, onto Italy. 

#parisfrance #eiffeltower #lemarais #catacombs #chezjanou #guysavoy #montmartre #prettycities #cntraveler #tlpicks

📍Basta Pasta, NYC / @bastapastaristorante 

Over 12 years ago, @ivyjford took @dancingclare and I to Basta Pasta for a Christmas dinner. None of us could afford it, not because it’s super expensive, but because we were trying to make rent as interns. It was a memorable evening—we felt so fancy.

🥇So excited to announce that the social media and video teams at the American Museum of Natural History won two @AnthemAwards! This is a faction of the Webbys that celebrates mission-driven work. 

We won for our local awareness campaign, Get Vaxxed Under the Blue Whale—a social media campaign across five platforms—and our Viruses, Vaccines & COVID-19 online hub, which was created as part of an NYC Department of Health & Mental Hygiene initiative. The result? About 100k vaccinations administered at the Museum + some 40,000 pageviews on the hub. 

This was a historic campaign, and I’m thrilled to have been a small part of it. 🐋 

#smm #socialmediamanager #amnh #bluewhale #anthemawards #webby #uws #musesocial #museums

We stopped by good ol’ Katz Deli last time our parents were in town—Christopher was a fan. Haven’t been? 👇  
🥒When you walk in, you’re given a ticket. Don’t lose that! The staff mark up the ticket as you order, and you pay as you leave—if you lose the ticket, you pay a fee. 

🧄Order sandwiches with the cutters. If the first cutter has a long line, move on down. 

🥩Order the pastrami sandwich. Ask for it on rye bread with mustard. If it’s your first time eating here, nothing else is acceptable. 

🥒Tip your cutter a few bucks. He might give you a few slices of meat while you wait for the sandwich—you’re supposed to eat the sample with your hands. 

🧄Make sure to get pickles before leaving the cutting station. They have full sour and half sour—I like both, but prefer to sprinkle a little salt on the half sour ones. 

🥩Order beer, fries, and Dr. Brown’s sodas at the drink area (a separate line after the cutters). Sometimes there’s also a beer guy open at the very front of the restaurant. 

🥒If you want a to-go box, you have to get back in line near the fry/soda guy—last time there was a terrible wait in this line, so consider splitting a sandwich instead!

🧄Do counter service if it’s your first visit. That’s the experience. But there is a section with waiters in the back of the restaurant. You’ll need to tell the bouncer at the front if you want to be seated. 

🥩Pay on your way out!

The last two weeks have really been ~something.~ Ryan had sudden eye surgery on his good eye, leaving him with very little vision. It may return, but it’s a long story and a long process (macular degeneration). It will not just heal. He’s been an all star, but I know it’s been frustrating and isolating. 

He started feeling a little better last week and was able to join me at a work conference for one evening at the @twahotel. We drink cocktails, ate good food, and went for a late-night swim. He could see the lights of the planes as they landed on the tarmac in front of the pool. It was so refreshing to be out and about with my best friend, doing “normal” things, and testing out new skills. Ryan even took the subway home by himself. 

He has more doctor’s appointments this week. It’s possible there will be another surgery. But we’re just taking it one day at a time. ❤️

#twa #retroaesthetic #madmen #staycation #visionloss

You have thousands of restaurant options in NYC and only so many meals in a day. Here’s a gem if you’re looking for authentic Cantonese food in Chinatown. Notes for @greatnynoodletown: Cash only. No reservations, but the wait doesn’t usually exceed 15 minutes. Quick service. Open 7 days a week. Recently included in the New York Times list of 100 Best Restaurants in NYC 2023. When they serve you the oranges, that means it’s time to go. 🦀

According to the @50bestbars list, @doublechickenpleasenyc is the top bar in North America! 
✔️Arrive early. 
✔️Don’t sleep on the Bolognese Grilled Cheese—a complete indulgence. 
✔️You can’t go wrong with any of their specialty cocktails: If you’re craving salt, try the Cold Pizza. And if you want dessert in a glass—without a ton of sugar—the Key Lime Pie is a fun way to end your experience. 

We also enjoyed the Red Eye Gravy, the Waldorf Salad, and the Japanese Cold Noodle (featured above). Our bartender was awesome and gave us the “house shot” with mezcal, plum, and shiso. 

After all the fun, we stopped by Shu Jiao Fu Zhou (cash only) for pork dumplings and peanut noodles. Highly recommend the whole adventure🤪
